value.title: Trump slams McCabe as ex-FBI official testifies virtually
value.excerpt: President Trump on Tuesday slammed ex-FBI deputy director Andrew McCabe, urging Republicans not to let him “get away with totally criminal activity” as the former official testified virtually before the Senate Judiciary Committee.

value.title: Cindy McCain joins Joe Biden transition team advisory board
value.excerpt: Cindy McCain, the widow of Republican Sen. John McCain, is reportedly joining the board of Joe Biden’s presidential transition team

value.title: Chrissy Teigen, John Legend dance to anti-Trump anthem 'FDT' as song climbs charts following election
value.excerpt: Chrissy Teigen and John Legend played "FDT" multiple times after Joe Biden's projected victory over Donald Trump in the 2020 presidential election was announced.

value.title: AOC, others pushing for apparent blacklist of people who worked with Trump
value.excerpt: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez and others have encouraged the creation of an apparent blacklist of people who helped President Trump during his time in office.

value.title: David Bossie, Head of Trump Post-Election Legal Effort, Tests Positive for Covid-19
value.excerpt: David Bossie, a longtime confidant of President Trump whom the campaign tapped last week to lead its post-election legal efforts, tested positive for Covid-19 on Sunday, according to a person familiar with the matter.

value.title: McConnell backs Trump legal fight in election results
value.excerpt: The Trump campaign has mounted legal challenges and alleged voting irregularities or outright fraud in several states.

value.title: Ex-Israeli UN Ambassador Danon on what a Biden presidency means for Middle East peace
value.excerpt: Israel's former ambassador to the United Nations Danny Danon provided insight on Monday into what a Biden presidency could mean for Middle East peace.

value.title: Pence on 2020 race: ‘It ain’t over til it’s over...and this AIN’T over!’
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence on Monday rallied his staff, saying the 2020 presidential race “ain’t over,” as the Trump campaign mounts legal battles in a number of key battleground states where President-elect Joe Biden is leading.

value.title: Dr. Nicole Saphier raises concern for Biden pledging a 'draconian' universal mask mandate
value.excerpt: After giving credit to the qualifications of President-elect Joe Biden’s coronavirus advisory board, Fox News medical contributor Nicole Saphier raised a concern about their move to potentially suppress Americans' civil liberties.

value.title: Trump ‘has a duty’ to supporters to fight for ‘transparent’ review of ballots: Miranda Devine
value.excerpt: President Trump “has a duty” to “half of America which voted for him to look into” ballot-counting in the 2020 presidential election “so that it's all transparent,” New York Post columnist Miranda Devine told “Fox & Friends” on Monday.

value.title: Biden coronavirus team to include Rick Bright, ousted HHS official
value.excerpt: Rick Bright, the ousted Health and Human Services official, will be one of 10 advisory board members on Democratic President-elect Joe Biden's coronavirus task force, Biden's transition team announced on Monday.

value.title: Biden should support push for transparency in vote as ‘ultimate presidential act’: Turley
South Dakota Gov. Noem: Al Gore got his day in court -- Trump deserves the same consideration
value.excerpt: South Dakota Gov. Kristi Noem urged the country to “afford the 70.6 million Americans that voted for President Trump the same consideration" provided to former vice president Al Gore in the 2000 legal battle that resulted in a Supreme Court decision and a George W. Bush victory.

value.title: Trump campaign holds protest in Las Vegas to decry irregularities, claim ‘dead people,’ non-Nevadans voted
value.excerpt: The Trump campaign held a Sunday afternoon press conference outside the Clark County Elections Department in Las Vegas to denounce alleged irregularities in last week’s election.

value.title: 'Wonder Woman' star Lynda Carter celebrates Kamala Harris' win on 45th anniversary of the show
value.excerpt: Wonder Woman” actress Lynda Carter shared a congratulatory note to Vice President-elect Kamala Harris on a special day for fans of the superhero TV series.

value.title: Romney says Trump should 'follow every legal option he has,' but choose words 'carefully'
value.excerpt: Sen. Mitt Romney, R-Utah, has no problem with President Trump challenging the 2020 election results in court, but said that he should tone down his public rhetoric.

value.title: Buttigieg: Republican Senate would go against 'will of the people' by opposing Biden agenda
value.excerpt: Biden transition team member Pete Buttigieg said Sunday that even if they win enough races to maintain control of the Senate, Republicans would be opposing the will of the American people if they stand in the way of President-elect Joe Biden's agenda.

value.title: Harris: American voters chose 'hope, unity, decency and yes, truth'
value.excerpt: Sen. Kamala Harris, in her victory speech as vice president-elect, said that in Tuesday’s election voters had chosen “hope, unity, decency and yes, truth.”

value.title: Pro-Trump election Facebook group 'Stop the Steal' banned after calling for violence
value.excerpt: Facebook banned a pro-Trump group after posts suggesting "worrying calls for violence" surrounding the highly contentious results of the 2020 election.

value.title: Schumer sings 'God Bless America' after Biden projected winner
value.excerpt: Sen. Chuck Schumer celebrated President Trump's projected defeat by singing a rendition of "God Bless America," and telling the former Manhattan resident it's time to pack up and go home to his new home state of Florida.

value.title: Biden's inauguration during COVID-19: What the January event could look like
value.excerpt: Construction is already underway in Washington, D.C., in preparation for the presidential inauguration on Jan. 20, 2021. The date is set by the U.S. Constitution's 20th Amendment.

value.title: Flashback: Trump in October said, 'Could you imagine if I lose?'
value.excerpt: President Trump mocked the idea of losing to former Vice President Joe Biden during a campaign rally less than a month before Election Day, pointing to rival Joe Biden as the "worst candidate in the history of presidential politics."

value.title: Biden claims 'mandate' while election vs. Trump remains undecided
value.excerpt: Joe Biden didn't declare victory Friday night over President Trump in the race for the White House, but he emphasized that he's "going to win" the presidential election.

value.title: Bernie Sanders thanks, praises progressives for 'Biden's victory' before race is called
value.excerpt: Sen. Bernie Sanders thanked progressives Friday afternoon for aiding Democratic nominee Joe Biden’s 2020 presidential efforts – even with the race still too close to call.

value.title: Minnesota 'Squad' member says Trump attack on her during campaign was a mistake
value.excerpt: Rep. Ilhan Omar, D-Minn., on Thursday said Trump "effed around" in deciding to attack her as a way to win over Minnesota voters.

value.title: Trump Names Danly to Head FERC, Replacing Chatterjee
value.excerpt: Neil Chatterjee, who has backed policies in support of clean energy, is being replaced as head of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission by fellow commissioner James Danly.

value.title: Trump 'likely' to run again in 2024 if he loses: Mick Mulvaney
value.excerpt: Trump's former acting White House chief of staff Mick Mulvaney says the president isn't ready to bow out of politics.

value.title: If Trump loses, he will regret 'denigrating mail-in voting': York
value.excerpt: If President Trump loses the election to Joe Biden as current vote tallies indicate, he could regret warning against mail-in voting, Fox News contributor Byron York argued Friday.

value.title: Trump Jr. calls out '2024 GOP hopefuls' for 'total lack of action' in ballot-counting fight
value.excerpt: Donald Trump Jr. pressured potential 2024 GOP contenders to vocally support President Trump as the president continues to air often unfounded grievances about alleged voter fraud.

value.title: Trump's voter-fraud remarks draw criticism from some Republicans
value.excerpt: President Trump faced some pushback from his own party Thursday after warning about illegal voting and an attempt to "steal" the presidential election.
